HEADWORD: Sarcastical
<hw>Sar*cas"tic*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <def>Expressing, or expressed by,
sarcasm; characterized by, or of the nature of, sarcasm; given to the
use of sarcasm; bitterly satirical; scornfully severe;
taunting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What a fierce and <qex>sarcastic</qex> reprehension would this
have drawn from the friendship of the world!</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sarcastically</ent>⟦br⟧
